entry.title: Fix some incompatibilities with std::variant from narrowing
entry.content:
std::variant does not allow narrowing conversions. absl::variant didn't

quite get this right, which means narrowing conversions sometimes sneak

in.



The main non-obvious consequence is that std::variant

cannot be constructed from literals like 0 or 2. Such literals have type

int, and an int may be negative. These ints will not be negative, but

the language has lost this information by the time it calls the

std::variant constructor.



The fix is to write 0u or 2u. Those have type unsigned, which can

convert to size_t without narrowing.



Bug: 1373620

entry.title: Use kUnicodeSets (v regexp flag) in URLPattern
entry.content:
This CL follows the recent spec update in [1]. After this CL, the

regular expression works with the unicodeSet mode, which allows the API

to interpret set notations, multi-codepoint properties etc.



Actually, this CL ends up only adding the support for set notations. At

the moment the API doesn't accept unicode character class escape (\p{},

\P{}) [2], thus we wouldn't add the multi-codepoint match functionarity.



There are some incompatibility between "u" and "v", some patterns are

privously valid but now errors. However, from UMA the impact looks very

limited, it's only around 0.3% of the total constructor calls.



So this CL changes the default flag to "v". Also add a kill switch.



[1] https://github.com/WICG/urlpattern/issues/178

[2] https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Regular_expressions/Unicode_character_class_escape

entry.title: Provide a new access token when reconnecting to a session
entry.content:
Access tokens last ~1 hour so we can't persist these to disk and allow

users to reconnect after 1 hour. This means we need to generate a new

access token for each session.



I've plumbed this up to the CrdAdminSessionController as there are a

few options:

1. Refactor DeviceCommandStartCrdSessionJob::OAuthTokenFetcher out

of the existing class and call it in CrdAdminSessionController

as needed

2. Create a new OAuthTokenFetcher in //remoting for admin sessions

and use it rather than the 'Passthrough' fetcher

3. Update the Access token to have a longer lifetime

4. Some other solution which the Commercial CRD folks like better



Per discussion with the Commercial CRD team, we are going to go

with option #1 and they will handle the refactoring in their code

to provide a new access token for each reconnection.

entry.title: Deflake printer tests for PDF conversion failure
entry.content:
Printing on Windows involves conversion of PDF pages to a different

format. The handling of the conversion result happens on the UI

thread, where it is queued for spooling. The worker thread

periodically wakes up to check for more pages and do spooling for

however many pages are ready.



When fake failures of the PDF conversion are induced in the middle of a

print job, that job may or may not get cancelled before earlier pages

are spooled. This can lead to flaky tests if they check for the number

of times pages get rendered.



Since the number of pages which actually get spooled for Windows

rendering is not important for these tests, update the test helper

methods to ignore these events when checking if the test should quit.

There are other following events that can be used to know when it is

safe for the tests to terminate.



Update the tests to drop the check of the rendered printed page result.

Detection of the error will come in https://crrev.com/c/5011488, as a

separate fix to ensure the user gets notified that an error has

occurred.

display of the Safety Check half sheet before the previous display of

entry.title: [Extensions] Fix some event page metrics not emitting at correct time.

Metric involved (incremented):

Extensions.Events.DispatchToAckTime.ExtensionEventPage3



Before this would emit for all events sent to all listeners running in

the extension renderer process. This included when the event ran in the

lazy background page script, but also when it ran in listeners like (but

not limited to) popup scripts.



Metric now emits if the event ran in the lazy background page script

(specifically if the event has a listener in the lazy background

page script context when the event is fired).



Relies on assumption that only one ExtensionHost::OnEventAck() call will

be made per event per extension process.

entry.title: mac: speculative fix the fullscreen lockup
entry.content:
The trigger condition of this bug is still unknown, but this is a

potential event sequence that results in an infinite loop:



Assume two monitors A and B and the following happens in sequence:



0. B is on active space.

1. User switches space on A.

2. On A, NSToolbarFullScreenWindow becomes key

3. On B, we activate the browser window by -makeKeyAndOrderFront.

4. A space on A becomes active as a result of step 1

5. On B, NSToolbarFullScreenWindow becomes key as a result of step 3.

6. On A, we activate the browser window by -makeKeyAndOrderFront.

7. A space on B becomes active as a result of step 5.

8. goes to step 2 as a result of step 6.



The key of this happening is that there is a timing gap between a

NSToolbarFullScreenWindow becoming key and the space becoming active.

As a result, we activate the wrong browser window and enter a loop.



This CL speculatively fixes the bug by ensuring that the

NSToolbarFullScreenWindow that became key is on the same space of the

browser window being activated.



I verified the fix by running it locally for my workflow for hours. The

bug does not seem to reproduce anymore.

entry.title: Move LevenshteinDistance() to base/strings
entry.content:
The Levenshtein distance is a commonly used measure for the similarity

of two strings, a and b. It is defined as the minimum number of

insert/remove/replace operations to convert from a to b. It can be

computed with a well-known dynamic programming algorithm in O(|a|*|b|).



In Chromium, this measure currently used in Ash, Autofill and SSLErrors.

components/compose is also planning to use it.

This CL unifies existing usages by moving Autofill's implementation to

base/strings.



All three existing uses only test if the Levenshtein distance is below

some small constant k. In this case, the computation can improved to

O(min(|a|, |b|) * k + k), using a variant of the dynamic programming

algorithm. Autofill's algorithm actually implements this, using an

optional third parameter. This parameter is used to improve the runtime

of the two other use cases.



Code-technically, this CL:

- Defines a function LevenshteinDistance() for std::string_view and

std::u16string_view arguments using a templated implementation.

- Combines all existing unit tests in a base_unittest.

entry.title: Multiplanar: Update GLCommonImageBackingFactory::GetFormatInfo
entry.content:
Update GLCommonImageBackingFactory::GetFormatInfo to return a vector

of format info for multiplanar formats based on corresponding planes'

formats being supported. This avoids basing the logic in AngleVulkan

and GLTexture shared image backings on multiplanar format constants

and instead uses the formats channel format and plane configs for

returning vector of FormatInfos.



This allows us to decouple the reliance of supported format logic in

backings from multiplanar shared image constants (which assume certain

channel format and plane configs) to various combinations of channel

formats and plane configs which can be used with hardware GMBs

through software video decode for pixel upload (VideoResourceUpdater).

done by pinch.
